reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars An Attractive Case to Store Documents
reviews.reviewText: I got this because I have documents in small piles all over the place. When I want or need some document, I can't find it.Pros:Now everything can be centrally located.2) The case is very attractive (very nice color).3) Made of good quality materials.Cons:1) The carry handles are made of cloth webbing. Not the most comfortable in the hand. The edge of the webbing is perpendicular to the flesh of the palm.2) Over time, the webbing will get dirty from being handled (unless they are treated with some kind of Scotchguard, idk). A suggestion would be flat plastic handles that can be tucked away into the two side pockets for storage, or pulled up for use as needed.3) The interior pocket dividers are open at the bottom. This means smaller envelopes and receipts are going to sink to the bottom and get stuck down there between and underneath dividers. This needs some kind of webbed material frame to hold the dividers in place and create a pocket bottom between each set of dividers walls.

reviews.reviewText: When I first received this organizer, it looked too small for all of the papers I had planned to put in it. I was wrong!
